Romanian X-Captain Voted Best Foreign Player in Turkey
BUCHAREST , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- Gheorghe Hagi , former captain of the Romanian national soccer team , was voted the best 1998 foreign soccer player in Turkey .
According to Rompres , Hagi was elected the best 1998 foreign soccer player of the Turkish championship by the Turkish Association of Sports Journalists .
The 33 year-old striker , nicknamed Maradona of the Carpathians , retired in autumn 1998 to play on a contract until 1999 for the Turkish team Galatasaray of Istanbul .
